{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water in mixing bowl. Set Varoma dish in position, add cassava to it, making sure that some holes remain unobstructed so steam can circulate. Close Varoma and steam <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until cassava is very soft. Set Varoma aside. Empty mixing bowl, then rinse with cold water and dry.","Place cheese in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add cooked cassava and 1 tsp salt then mash <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl, cover and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place oil, onions, garlic cloves, red pepper and spring onions in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b> ","Add minced beef, ground cumin, 1 tsp salt, black pepper and tomato puree, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on mixing bowl lid to help prevent splashing then cook <b>7 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and allow to cool for 1 hour.","To make carimañolas, divide cassava mixture into 8 balls. Flatten each ball across the palm, place about 1 tablespoon of filling in the centre and gently fold cassava over to enclose filling. Shape into a diamond and finish off neatly.","In a frying pan, add oil to a depth of 2 cm and heat to frying temperature, around 130°C. Cook carimañolas for approx. 3 minutes each, turning often. Drain on paper towels, and serve warm or cool."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g water","700 g cassava, peeled, cubed (3 cm)","100 g Cheddar cheese, cut in pieces","2 tsp fine sea salt","15 gram oil, plus extra for frying","50 g onions, halved","2 garlic cloves","50 g red pepper, deseeded","30 g spring onions","150 g beef mince","1 tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground black pepper","20 g tomato purée"]}],"id":"r208376","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-wsE-8pUzyQA\/XZMu9eIZ-rI\/AAAAAAAAaL0\/vn8GB3HJC2ExOuyyhHyJ5A89fL4NF3L6gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_WAPOVGYwKTytCvj8.png","title":"Meat and Cheese Stuffed Cassava (Carimañolas de carne y de queso)","publishedAt":"2017-09-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"985 kJ \/ 235 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towels, frying pan, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Cassava is also known as yucca or manioc. It is a very versatile starchy root vegetable, popular in South America and Africa.","Serve meat patties as a party platter, or serve 2 each as a main course.","The carimañolas can be made ahead and frozen. Allow them to cool completely to room temperature, and then spread out on a metal tray to freeze. When they have frozen, place in resealable freezer bags and return to freezer. This keeps them separate.","Serve with a tomato salsa: place <b>1 tomato<b>, <b>1 red<b> chilli, <b>80 g olive<b> oil, <b>30 g lemon<b> juice, <b>1 garlic<b> clove and <b>10 g parsley<b>  in mixing bowl and chop <b><strong>5 sec\/speed 5<\/strong><b>.","Instead of the meat filling, use <b>150 g<b> diced mozzarella cheese for a vegetarian option."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h","8 pieces"]}